# CHANAKYA Radar

- Mission Control (CO-SPRINT-104): first screen = live CHANAKYA feed + **hero Radar only**. KPIs / snapshot sit **below the fold**.
- **Radar | Kanban** switcher lives in the **global header** (beside Notifications, before CHANAKYA AI) — not in page content.
- Tabs preserve scope / KPI focus / selection via shared workspace-tab store.
- Opportunity Preview = right **slide-over** (click outside closes); never permanently shrinks Radar.
- Blip colour = operational status; **distance from centre = stage ageing**; **✓ tick = worked today** (resets next calendar day via activity date).
- Live feed is operational guidance only — does **not** open CHANAKYA AI (use existing AI button).
- Page must always **naturally scroll** (Radar + Kanban). No fixed-height lock / clipped content.
- KPI click expands opportunity list below snapshot; quadrant click focuses + scrolls to snapshot.
- Collision-safe blip placement. Quadrant labels outside dial.
- Metric SSOT / Vector / Health scoring — never reimplemented in UI.
- Real-time: `subscribeLoanFilesUpdated` + 60s / `storage` fallback.
- Matrix retired. Kanban cards never draggable.
- Four quadrants: On Track (N) · Follow-up Required (E) · At Risk (S) · Needs Attention (W).
